- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on energy-efficient design in wireless networks, specifically in small cell networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with power allocation and bandwidth allocation, which are related to information theory. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper involves optimization and resource allocation, which are related to control systems. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions user Quality of Service, which is related to multimedia applications. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the least likely category as the paper does not mention any security or cryptography-related topics.
